uding St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]},{"name":"Elin","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Elen ."],"variants":[{"name":"Elen","meanings":["form of   Helen  , now also used outside Wales. It is identical with the Welsh vocabulary word <i>elen</i> ‘nymph’, but this is unlikely to be the origin. It is found in Welsh texts from an early period as an equivalent of <i>Helen</i>, for example as the name of the mother of Constantine, finder of the True Cross."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Elin Howel was born in 1250, in Wales. She had at least 2 sons with Gwilym ap Hywel."},"et":{"1250–":"1250–Surnud","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1286–Male":"1286–Surnud","1302–Male":"1302–Surnud","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","1302":"1302","1286":"1286","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","Traean Glas, Breconshire, Wales":"Traeanglas, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Traeanglas, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Traeanglas, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales"},"fi":{"1250–":"1250–Kuollut","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","1286–Male":"1286–Kuollut","1302–Male":"1302–Kuollut","1250–Female":"1250–Kuollut","1302":"1302","1286":"1286","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","Traean Glas, Breconshire, Wales":"Traeanglas, Breconshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Traeanglas, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Traeanglas, Breconshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","W